PREAMBLE
==============================================================================

PoSDK (Pose-only Software Development Kit) is a licensed software framework for spatial visual computing applications. This license governs the use of the PoSDK framework (the "Software"), which includes:

1. The PoSDK plugin development framework (open-source components)
2. Integration interfaces to the PoCore computation engine (closed-source)
3. Sample plugins, documentation, and build scripts


REQUIREMENTS:
1. ATTRIBUTION: You must cite the PoSDK project in any publications,
   presentations, or derivative works using one of the following references:

   @article{cai2019equivalent,
     title={Equivalent Constraints for Two-View Geometry: Pose Solution/Pure
            Rotation Identification and 3D Reconstruction},
     journal={International Journal of Computer Vision},
     volume={127}, pages={163--180}, year={2019},
     doi={10.1007/s11263-018-1136-9}
   }

   @article{cai2023pose,
     title={A Pose-only Solution to Visual Reconstruction and Navigation},
     journal={IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence},
     volume={45}, number={1}, pages={73--86}, year={2023},
     doi={10.1109/TPAMI.2021.3139681}
   }

2. NOTICE RETENTION: You must retain all copyright notices, this license,
   and disclaimers in all copies or substantial portions of the Software.


RESTRICTIONS:
✗ Removal of copyright notices or attribution requirements


